articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

Compact, flat, and easy to navigate, Florence was made for short getaways. And three days is just enough time to major architectural wonders, marvel at masterpieces of Western art, wander the cobblestone streets, and chill out with a cheeseboard and chianti. This itinerary is designed to balance the highlights (hello, Michelangelo) with a taste of la dolce vita (hello, gelato), which is why we’ve factored in leisurely breaks for resting your feet, tasting the cuisine, and taking in the atmosphere.

articleContent.title: Start here: these hotels will inspire your entire trip

seoInfo.metaDescription: When choosing a stay for your long-awaited vacation, the usual checklist comes to mind: good location, comfy room, and, if you’re lucky, a pool. But if the goal of your getaway is to explore someplace new, shouldn’t you expect cultural experiences and local flavor from your hotel, too?

They say two is better than one—and in Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo, that couldn’t be more true. Ixtapa is modern and vibrant, with luxury resorts, breathtaking views, and settings surrounded by lush tropical nature. Zihuatanejo, a Pueblo Mágico, offers cobblestone streets, deep-rooted traditions, and a laid-back coastal vibe. Together, they deliver a travel experience that’s as diverse as it is authentic—earning Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo its place among Mexico’s top beach destinations.

articleContent.title: The many pathways to peace in Hiroshima

seoInfo.metaDescription: Nestled in the southwestern part of Japan’s Honshu Island, Hiroshima Prefecture is embraced by the azure waters of the Seto Inland Sea. More than a destination, Hiroshima is a haven for those yearning to escape into a realm of beauty and tranquillity mixed with cultural richness. In Hiroshima, time slows and beckons you to linger longer, savouring not just the picturesque scenery but also a diverse array of peaceful yet uplifting experiences. You’ll uncover a profound sense of spiritual and emotional connection, whether in well-known tourist spots or the often-overlooked wonders that quietly await discovery. Within the depths of this immersive journey, a sense of inner calm reveals itself.

articleContent.title: How to walk the Las Vegas Strip at night

seoInfo.metaDescription: Whenever I’m in Las Vegas my absolute favorite pastime is walking the Strip at night. That’s when the city’s massive casino resorts are at their most mesmerizing, wowing even a repeat visitor like me with synchronized fountains and incredible replicas of world-famous landmarks made all the more dazzling by a gazillion neon and LED lights. While this could border on Disneyesque, the Strip’s edgy, anything-goes vibe makes it the ideal spot to get swept up in the city’s notorious sensory overload—which, as a New Yorker, I can relate to.
